*formula_31 is the diameter of the spherical object,
*formula_4 is the gravitational acceleration,
*formula_6 is the density of the fluid,
*formula_35 is the density of the object,
*formula_43 is the projected area of the sphere,
*formula_5 is the drag coefficient, and
*formula_10 is the characteristic velocity (taken as terminal velocity, formula_46).

Substitution of equations (–) in equation () and solving for terminal velocity, formula_2 to yield the following expression
In equation (), it is assumed that the object is denser than the fluid. If not, the sign of the drag force should be made negative since the object will be moving upwards, against gravity. Examples are bubbles formed at the bottom of a champagne glass and helium balloons. The terminal velocity in such cases will have a negative value, corresponding to the rate of rising up.

